{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782186661151,"sessionID":"ses_10d67ce83ffeqFdCHSu0VlDLX8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_00_vCMuISZTdlKso0A08NQe1990","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore existing GPIO mux drivers","prompt":"Explore the Linux kernel source tree at /tmp/tmp.R6TG01uHm4 to understand the GPIO subsystem and find any existing GPIO multiplexer drivers.\n\n1. Look at drivers/gpio/ directory structure\n2. Search for existing mux-related gpio drivers (grep for \"mux\" in drivers/gpio/Makefile and Kconfig)\n3. Read any existing gpio-mux* files if they exist\n4. Read the gpio-mux driver (drivers/gpio/gpio-mux.c) fully\n5. Look at include/linux/gpio/driver.h for the gpiochip structure\n6. Look at how mux controller API works (include/linux/mux.h or similar)\n7. Check how other GPIO drivers use mux controllers\n8. Also look at drivers/mux/ for MUX API\n\nReturn the full contents of:\n- drivers/gpio/gpio-mux.c (if it exists)\n- Any relevant mux header files\n- The key parts of the GPIO driver framework from include/linux/gpio/driver.h\n- How existing drivers handle get/set with mux\n\nThis is for research only - do NOT write any code.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"<task id=\"ses_10d678d9effevflSJ950O0jHSV\" state=\"completed\">\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive report of my findings from the Linux kernel source tree exploration.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `drivers/gpio/` Directory Structure\n\nThe directory contains 223 entries including:\n- ~180 individual GPIO controller drivers (`gpio-*.c`)\n- Core gpiolib files (`gpiolib.c`, `gpiolib-of.c`, `gpiolib-cdev.c`, etc.)\n- `Kconfig` and `Makefile`\n- **There is NO `gpio-mux.c` file** in `drivers/gpio/`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Search for MUX-Related GPIO Drivers in Makefile and Kconfig\n\n**`drivers/gpio/Makefile`**: No reference to \"mux\" at all.\n\n**`drivers/gpio/Kconfig`**: Only two incidental mentions (not mux drivers):\n- Line 538: GPIO Nomadik \"registers handle muxing (\"alternate functions\")\"\n- Line 819: GPIO SIOX \"GPIO pins are muxed with\"\n\n**There is no `CONFIG_GPIO_MUX` or any mux-related GPIO driver Kconfig entry.**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing gpio-mux* Files\n\nThe glob `**/gpio-mux*` found only the Devicetree binding:\n- `/tmp/tmp.R6TG01uHm4/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/mux/gpio-mux.yaml`\n\nThe actual GPIO-based multiplexer is implemented as a **MUX controller driver**, not a GPIO driver. It lives at:\n\n- `/tmp/tmp.R6TG01uHm4/drivers/mux/gpio.c`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Full Contents of `drivers/gpio/gpio-mux.c`\n\n**Does NOT exist.** As noted, the GPIO-controlled mux is `drivers/mux/gpio.c`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. GPIO Driver Framework - `include/linux/gpio/driver.h` (Key Parts)\n\nThe full file is 906 lines. Here are the critical structures:\n\n### `struct gpio_chip` (lines 402-515) -- The central GPIO controller structure:\n\n```c\nstruct gpio_chip {\n    const char          *label;\n    struct gpio_device  *gpiodev;\n    struct device       *parent;\n    struct fwnode_handle *fwnode;\n    struct module       *owner;\n\n    // Standard callbacks\n    int  (*request)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n    void (*free)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n    int  (*get_direction)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n    int  (*direction_input)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n    int  (*direction_output)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset, int value);\n    int  (*get)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n    int  (*get_multiple)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned long *mask, unsigned long *bits);\n    int  (*set)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset, int value);\n    int  (*set_multiple)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned long *mask, unsigned long *bits);\n    int  (*set_config)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset, unsigned long config);\n    int  (*to_irq)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int offset);\n\n    int  base;\n    u16  ngpio;\n    u16  offset;\n    const char *const *names;\n    bool can_sleep;\n\n#ifdef CONFIG_GPIOLIB_IRQCHIP\n    struct gpio_irq_chip irq;\n#endif\n#ifdef CONFIG_OF_GPIO\n    unsigned int of_gpio_n_cells;\n    bool (*of_node_instance_match)(struct gpio_chip *gc, unsigned int i);\n    int  (*of_xlate)(struct gpio_chip *gc, const struct of_phandle_args *gpiospec, u32 *flags);\n#endif\n};\n```\n\nKey registration functions:\n- `gpiochip_add_data(gc, data)` / `devm_gpiochip_add_data(dev, gc, data)`\n- `gpiochip_remove(gc)`\n- `gpiochip_get_data(gc)` -- retrieves driver-private data\n\n---\n\n## 6. MUX Controller API -- Full Header Files\n\n### `include/linux/mux/driver.h` (for MUX controller drivers)\n\n```c\n#ifndef _LINUX_MUX_DRIVER_H\n#define _LINUX_MUX_DRIVER_H\n\n#include <dt-bindings/mux/mux.h>\n#include <linux/device.h>\n#include <linux/ktime.h>\n#include <linux/semaphore.h>\n\nstruct mux_chip;\nstruct mux_control;\n\nstruct mux_control_ops {\n    int (*set)(struct mux_control *mux, int state);\n};\n\nstruct mux_control {\n    struct semaphore lock;\n    struct mux_chip *chip;\n    int cached_state;\n    unsigned int states;\n    int idle_state;\n    ktime_t last_change;\n};\n\nstruct mux_chip {\n    unsigned int controllers;\n    struct device dev;\n    int id;\n    const struct mux_control_ops *ops;\n    struct mux_control mux[] __counted_by(controllers);\n};\n\n#define to_mux_chip(x) container_of((x), struct mux_chip, dev)\n\nstatic inline void *mux_chip_priv(struct mux_chip *mux_chip)\n{\n    return &mux_chip->mux[mux_chip->controllers];\n}\n\nstruct mux_chip *mux_chip_alloc(struct device *dev, unsigned int controllers, size_t sizeof_priv);\nint mux_chip_register(struct mux_chip *mux_chip);\nvoid mux_chip_unregister(struct mux_chip *mux_chip);\nvoid mux_chip_free(struct mux_chip *mux_chip);\nstruct mux_chip *devm_mux_chip_alloc(struct device *dev, unsigned int controllers, size_t sizeof_priv);\nint devm_mux_chip_register(struct device *dev, struct mux_chip *mux_chip);\n\nstatic inline unsigned int mux_control_get_index(struct mux_control *mux)\n{\n    return mux - mux->chip->mux;\n}\n\n#endif\n```\n\n### `include/linux/mux/consumer.h` (for MUX consumers)\n\n```c\n#ifndef _LINUX_MUX_CONSUMER_H\n#define _LINUX_MUX_CONSUMER_H\n\nstruct device;\nstruct mux_control;\nstruct mux_state;\n\nunsigned int mux_control_states(struct mux_control *mux);\nint mux_control_select_delay(struct mux_control *mux, unsigned int state, unsigned int delay_us);\nint mux_state_select_delay(struct mux_state *mstate, unsigned int delay_us);\nint mux_control_try_select_delay(struct mux_control *mux, unsigned int state, unsigned int delay_us);\nint mux_state_try_select_delay(struct mux_state *mstate, unsigned int delay_us);\n\n// Inline wrappers with delay_us=0:\nint mux_control_select(struct mux_control *mux, unsigned int state);\nint mux_state_select(struct mux_state *mstate);\nint mux_control_try_select(struct mux_control *mux, unsigned int state);\nint mux_state_try_select(struct mux_state *mstate);\n\nint mux_control_deselect(struct mux_control *mux);\nint mux_state_deselect(struct mux_state *mstate);\n\nstruct mux_control *mux_control_get(struct device *dev, const char *mux_name);\nvoid mux_control_put(struct mux_control *mux);\nstruct mux_control *devm_mux_control_get(struct device *dev, const char *mux_name);\nstruct mux_state *devm_mux_state_get(struct device *dev, const char *mux_name);\n\n#endif\n```\n\n### `include/dt-bindings/mux/mux.h` (idle state constants)\n\n```c\n#ifndef _DT_BINDINGS_MUX_MUX_H\n#define _DT_BINDINGS_MUX_MUX_H\n\n#define MUX_IDLE_AS_IS      (-1)\n#define MUX_IDLE_DISCONNECT (-2)\n\n#endif\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. How Existing Drivers Handle get/set with MUX\n\n### MUX Controller Driver Pattern (providers)\n\n**`drivers/mux/gpio.c`** -- The GPIO-controlled mux (this IS what would be `gpio-mux.c` conceptually):\n\n```c\nstruct mux_gpio {\n    struct gpio_descs *gpios;\n};\n\nstatic int mux_gpio_set(struct mux_control *mux, int state)\n{\n    struct mux_gpio *mux_gpio = mux_chip_priv(mux->chip);\n    DECLARE_BITMAP(values, BITS_PER_TYPE(state));\n    u32 value = state;\n\n    bitmap_from_arr32(values, &value, BITS_PER_TYPE(value));\n    gpiod_multi_set_value_cansleep(mux_gpio->gpios, values);\n    return 0;\n}\n\nstatic const struct mux_control_ops mux_gpio_ops = {\n    .set = mux_gpio_set,\n};\n```\n\nThe probe function pattern:\n1. Count GPIOs with `gpiod_count(dev, \"mux\")`\n2. Allocate mux chip: `devm_mux_chip_alloc(dev, 1, sizeof(*mux_gpio))`\n3. Get the private data: `mux_gpio = mux_chip_priv(mux_chip)`\n4. Set ops: `mux_chip->ops = &mux_gpio_ops`\n5. Get GPIOs: `devm_gpiod_get_array(dev, \"mux\", GPIOD_OUT_LOW)`\n6. Set states: `mux_chip->mux->states = BIT(pins)`\n7. Optionally read `idle-state` property\n8. Register: `devm_mux_chip_register(dev, mux_chip)`\n\n**`drivers/mux/mmio.c`** -- Another mux controller driver with both `get` and `set`:\n\n```c\nstatic int mux_mmio_get(struct mux_control *mux, int *state)\n{\n    struct mux_mmio *mux_mmio = mux_chip_priv(mux->chip);\n    unsigned int index = mux_control_get_index(mux);\n    return regmap_field_read(mux_mmio->fields[index], state);\n}\n\nstatic int mux_mmio_set(struct mux_control *mux, int state)\n{\n    struct mux_mmio *mux_mmio = mux_chip_priv(mux->chip);\n    unsigned int index = mux_control_get_index(mux);\n    return regmap_field_write(mux_mmio->fields[index], state);\n}\n```\n\n### MUX Consumer Pattern (users of mux controllers)\n\n**Consumer -- `mux_control` API** (e.g., `drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-gpmux.c`):\n\n```c\nstruct mux {\n    struct mux_control *control;\n    bool do_not_deselect;\n};\n\n// In probe:\nmux->control = devm_mux_control_get(dev, NULL);\n\n// When switching:\nret = mux_control_select(mux->control, chan);\n// ...do something with the selected state...\nmux_control_deselect(mux->control);\n```\n\n**Consumer -- `mux_state` API** (e.g., `drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-omap.c`):\n\n```c\nstruct omap_i2c_dev {\n    struct mux_state *mux_state;\n    ...\n};\n\n// In probe:\nmux_state = devm_mux_state_get(&pdev->dev, NULL);\nomap->mux_state = mux_state;\nr = mux_state_select(omap->mux_state); // selects and locks\n\n// In remove:\nmux_state_deselect(omap->mux_state);   // deselects and unlocks\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. `drivers/mux/` -- Full MUX Subsystem\n\nThe MUX subsystem lives at `/tmp/tmp.R6TG01uHm4/drivers/mux/` and contains:\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `core.c` | MUX core: `mux_chip_alloc`, `mux_chip_register`, consumer APIs |\n| `gpio.c` | **GPIO-controlled mux** (the \"gpio-mux\" driver) |\n| `mmio.c` | MMIO/regmap bitfield-controlled mux |\n| `adg792a.c` | Analog Devices ADG792A/G I2C mux |\n| `adgs1408.c` | Analog Devices ADGS1408/1409 SPI mux |\n| `Kconfig` | `CONFIG_MULTIPLEXER`, `CONFIG_MUX_GPIO`, `CONFIG_MUX_MMIO`, etc. |\n| `Makefile` | Builds `mux-core.o`, `mux-gpio.o`, `mux-mmio.o`, etc. |\n\nThe Kconfig for the GPIO-controlled mux is `MUX_GPIO` (not in `drivers/gpio/Kconfig`):\n\n```\nconfig MUX_GPIO\n    tristate \"GPIO-controlled Multiplexer\"\n    depends on GPIOLIB || COMPILE_TEST\n    help\n      GPIO-controlled Multiplexer controller.\n      The driver builds a single multiplexer controller using a number\n      of gpio pins. For N pins, there will be 2^N possible multiplexer\n      states.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **No `gpio-mux.c` in `drivers/gpio/`** -- The GPIO-based mux is implemented as a MUX controller provider (`drivers/mux/gpio.c`), NOT as a GPIO driver.\n\n2. **GPIO drivers consuming mux controllers** -- Searching `drivers/gpio/` for `mux_control` / `mux_state` / `mux_chip` found **zero results**. No GPIO driver in this tree currently consumes a mux controller. (This means writing a new GPIO driver that uses the MUX API to indirect GPIO accesses through an external mux would be novel.)\n\n3. **Two distinct roles for mux**:\n   - **MUX controller driver** (e.g., `drivers/mux/gpio.c`): Implements `struct mux_control_ops { .set() }`. Registers via `mux_chip_alloc` + `mux_chip_register`. Private data via `mux_chip_priv()`.\n   - **MUX consumer** (e.g., `drivers/i2c/muxes/i2c-mux-gpmux.c`): Gets a `mux_control` (or `mux_state`) via `devm_mux_control_get()` / `devm_mux_state_get()`, then calls `mux_control_select()` / `mux_control_deselect()` to switch.\n\n4. **The `gpio_chip` struct** provides the `get`/`set`/`get_multiple`/`set_multiple` hooks that a GPIO driver implementing mux indirection would populate.\n\n5. **The `gpio-latch` driver** (`drivers/gpio/gpio-latch.c`) is the closest existing GPIO driver that performs a similar \"indirection\" pattern -- it uses raw GPIOs (not the MUX API) to implement a latch-based multiplexer.\n</task_result>\n</task>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_10d67ce83ffeqFdCHSu0VlDLX8","sessionId":"ses_10d678d9effevflSJ950O0jHSV","model":{"providerID":"opencode","modelID":"deepseek-v4-flash-free"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore existing GPIO mux drivers","time":{"start":1782186537576,"end":1782186661106}},"id":"prt_ef2986a0b00163E2rc3U6rbn74","sessionID":"ses_10d67ce83ffeqFdCHSu0VlDLX8","messageID":"msg_ef2985fdf001kCbSdjXW5m8oED"}}
