{"type":"text","timestamp":1782186963496,"sessionID":"ses_10d67ce83ffeqFdCHSu0VlDLX8","part":{"id":"prt_ef29ee2fc001ccBvMBglOMWJ9j","messageID":"msg_ef29ed5fa001s36ZQyZsCUM4pG","sessionID":"ses_10d67ce83ffeqFdCHSu0VlDLX8","type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was implemented:\n\n**`drivers/gpio/gpio-mux.c`** - A virtual gpiochip driver that maps N virtual GPIOs to a single real GPIO via a mux controller. For each GPIO operation, it selects the mux state matching the virtual line offset, performs the operation on the underlying GPIO, then deselects the mux.\n\nKey design:\n- **Probe**: Gets a `mux_control` and a `struct gpio_desc`, registers a `gpio_chip` with `ngpio = mux_control_states(mux)`, with per-line direction/value caches\n- **`get_direction`**: Returns cached direction (no mux access needed)\n- **`direction_input`/`direction_output`**: Selects mux, sets GPIO direction, updates cache, deselects mux\n- **`get`**: Returns cached value for outputs; for inputs: selects mux, ensures input direction, reads GPIO, deselects\n- **`set`**: Caches value, then for outputs: selects mux, sets GPIO direction+value, deselects\n- **`can_sleep = true`** since mux operations (semaphore) can sleep\n\n**`drivers/gpio/Kconfig`** - Added `GPIO_MUX` entry (depends on `MULTIPLEXER`)\n\n**`drivers/gpio/Makefile`** - Added `obj-$(CONFIG_GPIO_MUX) += gpio-mux.o`\n\nDevice tree binding:\n```\ncompatible = \"gpio-mux-controlled\";\nmux-controls = <&mux_controller>;\nmuxed-gpios = <&gpio 5 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;\n```","time":{"start":1782186959612,"end":1782186963478}}}
