{"type":"text","timestamp":1782186737562,"sessionID":"ses_10d73caccffeJObP2i94PboqoZ","part":{"id":"prt_ef29b73cc001zK6U2yPVDqeeKO","messageID":"msg_ef29b670b001GaXAqjqV6v9Kx8","sessionID":"ses_10d73caccffeJObP2i94PboqoZ","type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's what was created:\n\n**`drivers/gpio/gpio-line-mux.c`** - Virtual GPIO chip driver that provides 1-to-many mapping between virtual GPIOs and a single real GPIO via a mux controller.\n\nKey design:\n- Registers a `gpio_chip` with N virtual lines, where N is the number of entries in `gpio-line-mux-states`\n- Each virtual line corresponds to a mux state\n- GPIO operations (`get`/`set`/`direction_input`/`direction_output`) select the mux, access the shared GPIO, then deselect\n- Per-line direction and output value caching in bitmaps, initialized to input\n- Mutex protection for all operations\n- Uses `devm_` managed allocations throughout\n\nAdded to `drivers/gpio/Kconfig` (as `GPIO_LINE_MUX`) and `drivers/gpio/Makefile` in alphabetical order.\n\nThe DT binding already exists at `Documentation/devicetree/bindings/gpio/gpio-line-mux.yaml` with `compatible = \"gpio-line-mux\"` - no binding changes needed.\n\nExample DT usage:\n```dtd\n&mux {\n    gpio-line-mux-states = <0>, <1>, <3>;\n    mux-controls = <&sfp_gpio_mux>;\n    muxed-gpios = <&gpio0 2 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;\n    gpio-controller;\n    #gpio-cells = <2>;\n};\n```","time":{"start":1782186734540,"end":1782186737529}}}
